events.name: Stanford Cardinal at Oklahoma State Cowboys

headlines.description: Quinn Sharp hit a 22-yard field goal in overtime to give No. 3 Oklahoma State a 41-38 win over Andrew Luck and No. 4 Stanford in a wildly entertaining Fiesta Bowl on Monday night.

notes.headline: ROSE BOWL GAME PRESENTED BY VIZIO

headlines.description: Oregon's incredible offense busted up Wisconsin and the record books on the way to the Ducks' first Rose Bowl victory in 95 years.
headlines.shortLinkText: Oregon sprints past Wisconsin in Rose

events.name: Nebraska Cornhuskers at South Carolina Gamecocks

headlines.description: Connor Shaw threw two touchdown passes and South Carolina (No. 9 BCS, No. 10 AP) had six sacks as the Gamecocks shut out the Nebraska (No. 20 BCS, No. 21 AP) in the final three quarters of 30-13 win in the Capital One Bowl on Monday.

events.name: Michigan State Spartans at Georgia Bulldogs

headlines.description: Kirk Cousins threw for 300 yards and one touchdown and Dan Conroy kicked a 28-yard field goal in the third overtime, giving Michigan State a 33-30 victory over Georgia in the Outback Bowl on Monday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Michigan St. derails UGA in 3OTs at Outback

events.name: Houston Cougars at Penn State Nittany Lions

headlines.description: Penn State's tumultuous year ended with a 30-14 loss to Houston in the TicketCity Bowl on Monday, a dispiriting finish to a season in which coach Joe Paterno was fired as part of a child sex-abuse scandal that shook college sports.
headlines.shortLinkText: Penn St. ends trying season in defeat

events.name: Ohio State Buckeyes at Florida Gators

headlines.description: Florida's special teams came up big in the Gator Bowl, scoring twice as the Gators beat Ohio State 24-17 on Monday in a game between Urban Meyer's old team and his future one.
headlines.shortLinkText: Florida stops Ohio State in Gator Bowl
